Description: This package designed for analyzing deconvolution of the bulk sample(s) 
    using an atlas of reference signature profiles and a user-selected model (non-negative 
    least squares, support vector, quadratic programming, or robust linear model). Users
    can upload or can expand their own reference atlases using the findSignatures function,
    or can use the atlas provided in the package. simulateCellMix function included to 
    simulate a bulk signature profile of a given size. Additionnaly, BSmeth2Probe function
    can be used to map methylation data to probe IDs.
